I had downloaded a program that stacks the frames vertically into a single collage picture.<br />It was an animation frame editor. It looked good..<br />Was going to try it out fully on weekend. <br />Last night, for some unknown reason Win 10 decided to not boot and killed my drive trying to repair it.<br />Got it working again from an image from a year ago, but forgot about saving that program.<br />Now I don't remember what it was called. There are probably lots out there. <br />I didn't even know my old Adobe Elements could split a gif into layers until last week. <br />Probably can make a vertical filmstrip too, without the photo merge aspect. <br /><br />Bet you p3y0t3 knows the best and easiest program.<br /><br />TigerNightmare uses a morph function of the GAP plugin with GIMP.<br /><br />Vertical frame compilers, they are probably right under our noses in image editor programs we use.<br /><br />For me I did the cat one the hard way.  <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" /> <br />I put corner registraion marks for each frame for lining up the transparent frames, as layers.<br />Then merged into one png.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Wed Mar 30, 2016 3:40 pm</p><hr />
